{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"302c5f25-8f05-44dd-b879-5e6c7f85ee2f","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it now uses MTP under the hood.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (2.9.3) — only the **runner** changes.\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property lets `dotnet test` work with MTP.\n- Your test project now also produces a **standalone executable** you can run directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d522b47-775b-4910-b9c0-b629d517b8db","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":342,"requestId":"D007:1EB7:1B8FC92:1F7A083:69EC0E89"},"id":"466d5973-31c6-46cd-895c-0c15202a075e","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:45:04.708Z","parentId":"0d152927-5f6c-4d32-bd98-ce9bee4f2919"}
